demo/Min_quadrilateral_2/README
-------------------------------

Interactive demo programs of some optimisation algorithms in CGAL.
Input (mouse clicks) and output are visualized in a LEDA window.

The provided makefile is prepared to link with LEDA.  

The demo is based on GeoWin, for information about the standard
features of the geowin interface, please refer to the GeoWin
documentation.


minimum_enclosing_quadrilateral_2_demo:

shows the minimum enclosing rectangle(orange), parallelogram(blue) and
strip(green) of a planar point set. A strip is the closed region
between two parallel lines. Click the left mouse button to add points,
and hold it to drag a point around. There are various options for
generating test data, loading and saving scenes and changing the
appearance.

Michael Hoffmann
